{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcwdsUQGsDeGiphkWYUEY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KU6Q9xc1L9VKPSaygaAPiz","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2sonnet-run-without-lessons-ledger--ll1-r2/memory/staging_debug_flag_incident.md","content":"---\nname: staging-debug-flag-incident\ndescription: Staging config had DEBUG=true which silently swallowed errors, causing a 2-hour debugging detour\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nStaging config previously had `DEBUG=true`, which silently swallowed all errors instead of surfacing them. This cost ~2 hours of debugging time on 2026-07-11 before the actual root cause (not the flag itself) was found. The flag has since been fixed/removed.\n\n**Why:** DEBUG mode in this project's config apparently changes error-handling behavior (swallowing errors) rather than just verbosity — surprising and non-obvious from the name alone.\n\n**How to apply:** If a future bug in staging seems to produce no errors/logs where you'd expect them, check the staging config for `DEBUG` or similar flags early rather than assuming the code path is silently succeeding.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":257,"cache_read_input_tokens":32548,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":257},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1743d7cd-54c8-4773-8557-01faf16043b7","uuid":"8df8f24a-8785-4a8d-b35d-c0f6b2b43323","request_id":"req_011CcwdsSmYZyrZfeRA6418i"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KU6Q9xc1L9VKPSaygaAPiz","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2sonnet-run-without-lessons-ledger--ll1-r2/memory/staging_debug_flag_incident.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1743d7cd-54c8-4773-8557-01faf16043b7","uuid":"83659a7b-ea0c-4161-81ea-9b9e025bdaf3","timestamp":"2026-07-12T05:47:43.959Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2sonnet-run-without-lessons-ledger--ll1-r2/memory/staging_debug_flag_incident.md","content":"---\nname: staging-debug-flag-incident\ndescription: \"Staging config had DEBUG=true which silently swallowed errors, causing a 2-hour debugging detour\"\nmetadata: \n  node_type: memory\n  type: project\n  originSessionId: 1743d7cd-54c8-4773-8557-01faf16043b7\n---\n\nStaging config previously had `DEBUG=true`, which silently swallowed all errors instead of surfacing them. This cost ~2 hours of debugging time on 2026-07-11 before the actual root cause (not the flag itself) was found. The flag has since been fixed/removed.\n\n**Why:** DEBUG mode in this project's config apparently changes error-handling behavior (swallowing errors) rather than just verbosity — surprising and non-obvious from the name alone.\n\n**How to apply:** If a future bug in staging seems to produce no errors/logs where you'd expect them, check the staging config for `DEBUG` or similar flags early rather than assuming the code path is silently succeeding.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
